 :tx/rationale "Set t-30f5d046 title=PERF-4: Session daemon with Unix socket. REVISED: Store loading is already cached (1.4s). The daemon's primary value is keeping COMPUTED STATE (routing, fitness, coherence, task counts) hot in memory and updating incrementally on each new txn — eliminating the O(tasks*datoms) recomputation that causes 30s status. ARCHITECTURE: (1) braid daemon start: fork background, bind .braid/daemon.sock, load store from cache, compute routing/fitness ONCE. (2) On new txn file (inotify/kqueue on .braid/txns/): parse new txn, append to in-memory store, INCREMENTALLY update routing (re-score only affected tasks) and fitness (delta computation via MaterializedViews). (3) On status request via socket: return pre-computed snapshot (<1ms). (4) On explicit invalidation (braid harvest, schema change): full recompute. (5) Session lifecycle: daemon starts on first braid command if not running, stops on braid harvest --commit. (6) Graceful fallback: if daemon not running, use PERF-2 disk cache path. (7) W-alpha (agent working set): read-command provenance stored in daemon memory, flushed to separate journal on session end (INV-STORE-014). ACCEPTANCE: (A) status with daemon: <100ms. (B) status without daemon: <2s (PERF-2 cache fallback). (C) Daemon handles concurrent clients. (D) Clean shutdown writes cache + flushes W-alpha. (E) PID file prevents double-start. (F) Auto-start on first command, auto-stop on harvest. DEPENDS-ON: PERF-2. TRACES: ADR-STORE-006 (revised). FILE: crates/braid/src/daemon.rs (new) + crates/braid/src/commands/mod.rs"
